Manchester City manager Pep Guardiola has urged his squad to remain positive ahead of Sunday's crucial final match of the season against Aston Villa where a win would see City retain the Premier League title. City are top of the league with 90 points as they head to the final game, just one point ahead of Liverpool who have a date with Wolves. Liverpool and Manchester City take the battle for glory to the last day after City blew a chance to retain the league title with a game in hand when they drew 2-2 away to West Ham United.